                    <p><strong>August 26th, 2021</strong></p>

                    <h5>Sangeet and Garba <span class="time">5PM - 11PM</span></h5>
                    <p>Among the many pre-wedding events that occur prior to South Asian wedding ceremonies,
                        the <b>Sangeet</b> is where the party begins. Friends and family perform songs and
                        choreographed
                        dances for the bride and groom as part of the wedding celebrations. It'll be a fun and
                        crazy night full of dancing!
                        <br>
                        <br>
                        <b>Garba</b> is a form of circular dance that originated in Gujarat (where Ankur's family is
                        from). People dance around the center in a circle making sweeping motions with their arms.
                        This routine is followed by Dandhiya Raas, which is a structured dance with
                        wooden sticks. We'll have a little intro and tutorial so you can join in!
                        You can also prepare by watching <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=M2GO52YmBek">this
                            video.</a></p>
                </div>
            </div>
